{"name":"Short Burst","permission":{"default":0,"A9LyAqagoJJU3gDH":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.GaKxs9k9VSIHQadj"}},"content":"<p>The Electric Samurai&rsquo;s gun fires Short Bursts. Each attack against a target expends 3 bullets, but grants a +2 bonus to hit. A roll of 1 Disconnects as usual, but a roll of 2 causes the weapon to malfunction. It may not be fired again until the character uses an Action (no test necessary) to fix the problem.</p>","_id":"7Af9s2g1GlkytrNY"}
{"_id":"9l3qvlJ9eFizcEor","name":"Managing Cards","permission":{"default":0,"A9LyAqagoJJU3gDH":3},"folder":"","flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.TPyO53xtRrYkVoQD"}},"content":"<p>Currently, cards in the Torg Eternity system are handled through the Unofficial Card Support module, which is automatically installed with the base system.</p>\n<h2>Guide for Players</h2>\n<p>To manage your cards, click on the card menu near the lower left-hand corner of your screen:</p>\n<p><img src=\"modules/te001-up-the-creek/images/card-menu.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"331\" height=\"199\" /></p>\n<p>From there, you can click the card-shaped icon to interact with the various decks:</p>\n<p><img src=\"modules/te001-up-the-creek/images/card-icon.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"62\" height=\"52\" /></p>\n<p>The menu for interacting with the decks will look like this:</p>\n<p><img src=\"modules/te001-up-the-creek/images/decks-menu.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"254\" height=\"123\" /></p>\n<p>Click on the hand icon to draw cards, the eye icon to view cards in the deck, and the outbox icon to view the discard pile.</p>\n<p>Once you have drawn a hand of cards, you can take various actions with them by right clicking on them:</p>\n<p><img src=\"modules/te001-up-the-creek/images/cards-options.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"227\" height=\"576\" /></p>\n<p>You place a card in your pool by \"marking\" it.</p>\n<p>Please note that, as a player, you can drag a card onto the desktop. However, once you do so, you will lose control of the card, and only the GM will be able to take actions with the card.</p>\n<h2>Guide for GMs</h2>\n<p>GMs have some additional options when handling cards and decks. To manage decks of cards, drag the folder for the deck from the items menu onto the desktop.</p>\n<p>To interact with the deck, you will need to click on the tile controls option in the upper left hand corner of Foundry.</p>\n<p><img src=\"modules/te001-up-the-creek/images/tile-controls.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"220\" height=\"574\" /></p>\n<p>From there, you can right click on the decks to interact with them. Among other things, you will have the options to draw, reset, shuffle, or view the decks.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>"}
{"_id":"B2TKLzGGeXvc1ZU1","name":"Multi-Actions","permission":{"default":0,"A9LyAqagoJJU3gDH":3},"folder":"","flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.VGndHNofrt5cyZqK"}},"content":"<p>A Storm Knight may try to do two (or more) different actions on the same turn, for example tricking one foe and then attacking another. Multiactions are simultaneous, so the results of an interaction attack don&rsquo;t apply in time to help an attack made at the same time. A &ndash;2 penalty applies to every action for each extra attempted. Only <em>one </em>roll is attempted, and the bonus generated applies to each action separately. Don&rsquo;t bother introducing this concept until a player asks to do something that is best expressed as a Multi-Action or the Approved Action is Multi-Action.&nbsp;</p>"}
{"_id":"BGpU76zitnb1LnzH","name":"The Bonus Chart","permission":{"default":0,"A9LyAqagoJJU3gDH":3},"folder":"","flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.YgNCKbstWNvoJVtS"}},"content":"<p>The Bonus number in Torg Eternity is calculated using the Bonus Chart. The Foundry system for Torg Eternity will automatically look up your bonus number based on the result of your dice rolls. To manually calculate a bonus, or to understand how an additional Possibilty might affect your bonus number, consult the chart below:</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>BONUS CHART</strong></p>\n<table style=\"height: 73px; width: 99.3356%;\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 6.81282%;\">Die<br />Roll</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 5.6661%;\">1</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 3.6425%;\">2</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 3.6425%;\">\n<p>3</p>\n<p>4</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 3.6425%;\">\n<p>5</p>\n<p>6</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 3.6425%;\">\n<p>7</p>\n<p>8</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 4.31703%;\">\n<p>9</p>\n<p>10</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 4.31703%;\">\n<p>11</p>\n<p>12</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 4.31703%;\">\n<p>13</p>\n<p>14</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 4.31703%;\">15</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 4.31703%;\">16</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 4.31703%;\">17</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 4.31703%;\">18</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 4.31703%;\">19</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 4.31703%;\">20</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 4.31703%;\">\n<p>21</p>\n<p>25</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 4.31703%;\">\n<p>26</p>\n<p>30</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 4.31703%;\">\n<p>31</p>\n<p>35</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 4.31703%;\">\n<p>36</p>\n<p>40</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 4.45194%;\">\n<p>41</p>\n<p>45</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 4.45194%;\">\n<p>46</p>\n<p>50</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 4.45194%;\">+5</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 6.81282%;\">-10</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 5.6661%;\">-10</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 3.6425%;\">-8</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 3.6425%;\">-6</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 3.6425%;\">-4</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 3.6425%;\">-2</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 4.31703%;\">-1</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 4.31703%;\">0</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 4.31703%;\">1</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 4.31703%;\">2</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 4.31703%;\">3</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 4.31703%;\">4</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 4.31703%;\">5</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 4.31703%;\">6</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 4.31703%;\">7</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 4.31703%;\">8</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 4.31703%;\">9</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 4.31703%;\">\n<p>10</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 4.31703%;\">11</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 4.45194%;\">12</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 4.45194%;\">13</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 4.45194%;\">+1</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>"}
