{"_id":"UdOHo3I4piwEd6vO","name":"Interaction Attack","permission":{"default":0,"A9LyAqagoJJU3gDH":3},"folder":"","flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.sFKinwBNA5eTFoNT"}},"content":"<p>Interaction attacks may be based on any of the following for skills: <em>intimidation </em>(threatening foes), <em>maneuver </em>(feinting and weaving), <em>taunt </em>(verbal goading), and <em>trick </em>(clever uses of the environment). Interactions function the same way. Pick a target and make a test. The DN for the test is equal to the target&rsquo;s total in the same skill, so trick vs trick, maneuver vs maneuver, etc. If the attacker succeeds the target is either Stymied (&ndash;2 on tests) or Vulnerable (all attacks and interactions are +2 against that target) until the end of their next turn. On a Good success the target is Very Stymied (&ndash;4) or Very Vulnerable (+4), or both Stymied (&ndash;2) and Vulnerable (+2)&hellip;attackers choice! An Outstanding result is called a Player&rsquo;s Call. The Good effect still applies, plus the player and GM negotiate an additional effect. This might be as potent as a weaker foe fleeing the battle or being taken out by the environment. A stronger foe might not be completely removed by a Player&rsquo;s Call, but should suffer either a permanent effect or at least losing an action. Gospog are immune to intimidate and taunt, so explain interactions once maneuver or trick are Approved as a way to get Destiny Cards and to show off how effective interactions can be!&nbsp;</p>"}
{"_id":"XEYr34ZyAggBFLI8","name":"The Living Land Table Tent","permission":{"default":0,"A9LyAqagoJJU3gDH":3},"folder":"","flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.kbcDGBaYUu20FWSK"}},"content":null,"img":"modules/te002-up-the-creek/images/living-land-card.jpg"}
{"_id":"jpwOVLoQXh4xjn7q","name":"04 - Scene Two:  Land Ho!","permission":{"default":0,"A9LyAqagoJJU3gDH":3},"folder":"","flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.LNXI539r3NK8Hmno"}},"content":"<p>The boat reaches the wreckage of the bridge, and now the Storm Knights must disembark and make their way through the steamy jungles of the Living Land on foot. This is a Dramatic Scene, and the Storm Knights can feel the tension in the air as they begin their search for the stela.</p>\n<p>Read aloud or paraphrase the following:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>&ldquo;No enemies greet you at the shore, but tracks of the large, three toed feet of edeinos abound, and the distant roar of a massive dinosaur hints of dangers lurking among the massive jungle trees. The situation is tricky. There are hundreds of edeinos in the area. The Storm Knights must follow the trails in the area and find the stela before the majority of the creatures find them!&rdquo;</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>For this Torg Eternity scene, use the Main Foundry scene that is included with this module.</p>\n<h2>FIRST DRAMATIC SKILL RESOLUTION</h2>\n<p>In Torg Eternity, a situation like this can be played out as a Dramatic Skill Resolution. The team has five rounds (Drama Cards) to complete the mission, which consists of four different steps. After five rounds, enough edeinos flood the area that the Storm Knights must retreat to the boat in failure. However if the team completes all four steps in five rounds or fewer they escape back to the boat before any large warbands arrive. The steps for the task are:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>A</strong>: Follow the trails to the correct area. This is a <em>tracking </em>test, DN 10. Most of the heroes don&rsquo;t have tracking, but they could still make the attempt (Unskilled) using <em>Mind </em>with no adds.</li>\n<li><strong>B</strong>: Sneak past the main edeinos encampment to the stela&rsquo;s location. This is a challenging (DN 12) <em>stealth </em>test. If a character doesn&rsquo;t have <em>stealth</em>, <em>Dexterity </em>is the attribute for Unskilled attempts.</li>\n<li><strong>C</strong>: Cut through the thick underbrush to reach the stela. This is a DN 10 <em>survival </em>test. Survival is based on <em>Mind</em>. Note that the Realm Runner has a Machete which makes <em>survival </em>Favored. On a Favored test, if you don&rsquo;t like the first die roll, you may roll again&mdash;but you must accept the new result, even if it&rsquo;s worse!</li>\n<li><strong>D</strong>: Sense whether the stela is active, or has any special defenses. This is a DN 14 <em>reality </em>test. Every Storm Knight has reality, which is based on <em>Spirit</em>.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Flip over a new Drama Card to indicate the task has started. This is a Dramatic Scene now, so use the Dramatic line for initiative and effects. The block on the side that was ignored earlier now becomes critical. Letters A through D may appear there, along with different problems called Dilemmas. During a DSR a step may only be attempted its letter appears on the card, and each step must be performed in order. So if Step A appears, a Storm Knight may attempt the <em>tracking </em>test.</p>\n<p>Only one Storm Knight can attempt a step during the round. Others may help by Combining their actions. Each chooses: grant the lead Storm Knight a simple +1 bonus&mdash;or attempt the test and grant nothing on a failure, a +1 bonus on a success, +2 on a Good success, or +3 on an Outstanding success. A DSR is an encounter, which means cards may only be played from the Action Pool.</p>\n<p>The Storm Knights should choose who is attempting the step and let anyone else go first to stack up bonuses or get Supporter Destiny Cards into their Action Pools. If the lead fails the skill test can&rsquo;t be attempted again that round. A different character may take the lead on every round.</p>\n<p>Also, this DSR isn&rsquo;t happening undisturbed. Small bands of edeinos to skirmish with the Storm Knights, see below. Some of the band must fight off the villains while others work on completing the task. The cards in play and number of Possibilities may be even more important than the character&rsquo;s skills, so be flexible!</p>\n<h3>Multiple Steps</h3>\n<p>If multiple steps are available on the card, the lead Storm Knight may Multi-Action to attempt both steps. Roll a single bonus and apply it to both skill values, with an extra &ndash;2 Penalty for each extra action. So if Step A was already resolved and the next Drama Card listed both B and C the character taking the lead that turn could roll once with a &ndash;2 penalty and generate a total for both stealth and survival. Note that a Flurry gives the whole team an extra turn, which means two different steps might be attempted, and a different character might lead the second attempt!</p>\n<h3>Dilemmas</h3>\n<p>If a Dilemma appears on the card it counts as the current step being available (A if you&rsquo;re just starting, B if you&rsquo;ve completed A, and so on), but there&rsquo;s a consequence for failure. Not trying at all for the round counts the same as failing!</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Complication</strong>: A strange mist creeps through the valley with the stela, making navigation much harder depending on where the group is approaching from. If the step fails all future tests against the DSR suffer a &ndash;1 penalty.</li>\n<li><strong>Potential Setback</strong>: A larger warband arrives in the area and the heroes must flee and find another route. The last step that was completed is lost. So if the group was testing for step C they now must complete step B again instead.</li>\n<li><strong>Critical Problem</strong>: The edeinos swarm the area in numbers, drawn by the noise and activity. The Storm Knights must circle around completely to try again. Any completed steps are lost.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Last Ditch Effort</h3>\n<p>If it&rsquo;s the fifth round and the steps aren&rsquo;t present to complete the task, all isn&rsquo;t lost. The team can try a Last Ditch Effort. This is a Multi-Action that must attempt every remaining step, and suffers an extra &ndash;2 penalty. So if steps B, C, and D were still left the Last Ditch Effort would suffer a &ndash;6 penalty to all three skills. Choose the lead for this last attempt carefully!</p>\n<h2>EDEINOS SKIRMISHERS</h2>\n<p>To complicate the Dramatic Skill Resolution above, edeinos skirmishers harass the heroes at every step of the way, hoping to delay them until the main warband arrives. At the start of the first round place one Edeinos Warrior for each Storm Knight on the table. Even though there is no map for this scene, placing tokens is a good way to help the players keep track how many edeinos are present and roughly where they are. The edeinos emerge from the thick jungle about 10 meters away from the Storm Knights. On their first turn they move halfway towards the heroes and throw spears (missile weapons), and then move into melee combat range on subsequent turns. If Attack is an Approved Action they run to get into melee range so they can All-Out Attack!</p>\n<p>Each round, at the beginning, another two Edeinos Warriors appear to join the battle. If the heroes suffer a Setback four warriors appear instead! If the villains suffer a setback they receive no reinforcements. If the villains act first, one of the warriors may attempt an Interaction Attack against the lead Storm Knight to Stymie (&ndash;2) attempts to gain steps!</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[te002-up-the-creek.up-the-creek-actors.IE5R3CvPVcYV2Plv]{Edeinos Warrior} (1 per Storm Knight)</li>\n<li>@Compendium[te002-up-the-creek.up-the-creek-actors.IE5R3CvPVcYV2Plv]{Edeinos Warrior} (2 at the beginning of each subsequent round)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>When the Edeinos Warriors appear, show the players the @Compendium[world.up-the-creek.IpLfFI1PqX5cREIb]{Edeinos Threat Stand}.</p>\n<h3>Mobs</h3>\n<p>Unlike the Gospog, edeinos suffer Shock. With lots of villains on the table it&rsquo;s recommended that the GM takes any Shock damage in one pile, and every time 10 Shock accumulates remove the most appropriate warrior, usually the one who was last attacked. A blow that Defeats an edeinos with a Wound doesn&rsquo;t affect this pile one way or another</p>\n<h2>IF THE DRAMATIC SKILL RESOLUTION FAILS</h2>\n<p>Read aloud or paraphrase the following:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>&ldquo;More and more scaly lizardmen burst through the trees each second, and it&rsquo;s clear the only chance for survival is to run back to the boat as quickly as possible and flee the area. There are cries and thrown spears clatter off the sides of the vessel as it speeds downriver back towards the coast, but everyone makes it aboard and back to the carrier. You&rsquo;re disappointed that you didn&rsquo;t get close enough to learn about the stela, but there will be other missions, other chances to show the invaders that they aren&rsquo;t invincible.&rdquo;</p>\n</blockquote>\n<h2>IF THE DRAMATIC SKILL RESOLUTION SUCCEEDS</h2>\n<p>Read aloud or paraphrase the following:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>&ldquo;As you get near the stone monolith you can feel a low, pulsing energy within it, similar to what you feel crossing into the Living Land. As you reach out towards it words and images start flooding into your mind. Backup. This would mark a boundary for the Living Land if one of the main stelae were uprooted. They CAN be uprooted. Devastation. The transformation back to Core Earth reality is violent and obliterates the ordinary people inside the area who have transformed&mdash;unless the Storm Knights have flooded the area with Possibility Energy first. The energy that comes from stories, stories of hope and resistance. The same energy that these stelae slowly absorb and send&hellip;somewhere. As you concentrate you feel it, this stela is attached to a network that stretches out in every direction. A spider&rsquo;s web. And at the center of the web a presence of absolute darkness. You hear the name Rec Pakken in whispers, and with a shiver you feel that the darkness is now looking directly at you!</p>\n<p>&ldquo;You break connection quickly. It&rsquo;s time to go. Reinforcements are coming, and not just the army of edeinos camped nearby. Everyone rushes back to the boat with edeinos scouts close behind, but you all board and flee downriver before the forces of darkness can strike. You&rsquo;ve learned something about the invaders, and have the exact location of this backup stela marked. With this information you and the Delphi Council can start the long fight to reclaim the Earth!&rdquo;</p>\n</blockquote>"}
